        detail: [{ title: ' Ⅰ. Definition and change of certification services', content: ['The vertification service is such a service where merchants enjoy certain privileges and undertake certain obligations in the platform after merchants provide authentic and credible identity information and pay a certain amount of security deposit. Unless there is a statutory situation or otherwise agreed in this agreement, once you have completed the vertification on the platform, the corresponding identity information and certification results will not be modified or cancelled for any reason; if your identity information has changed after the vertification is completed, You should provide the platform with the vertificate issued by the corresponding department, and the platform will help you to change your certification information.', 'In order to provide better service and secure transaction security, the platform has the right to modify or adjust the contents of this agreement according to the changes in subjective and objective conditions, and announces the changed text of this agreement by the platform without separate notification. After making any modifications or changes to this agreement, you will continue to use the services provided by the platform, that is, you have read, understood and agreed to accept the contents of the changed agreement; If you do not agree with the content of the changed agreement, you should immediately apply to disable the vertification service to the platform.'] }, { title: 'Ⅱ. The merchant rights of vertification', content: ['The platform will provide a unique vertification merchant mark to the merchant successfully applying for vertification, and the mark can distinguish between the uncertified merchant on the platform.', 'Publish the transaction advertisement information that meets the requirements on the platform.'] }, { title: 'Ⅲ. Required information and deposit for vertification', content: ['Personal information of the merchant: Please complete the attachment business application information and upload.', 'Asset security deposit: Merchant applying successfully for vertification should pay a certain deposit to the platform. The deposit will be transferred to the deposit account to which the certified merchant belongs. The certified merchant cannot process or transfer funds in the account within a certain period of time.'] }, { title: 'Ⅳ. The use of vertification materials', message: 'Report of vertification materials: the vertification materials that you submit to the platform at the time of vertification, that is, irrevocably authorize to be retained by this platform. Except as required by law or as agreed in this agreement, the platform promises not to edit or publish your certification materials to any third party and not to use it for commercial purposes, except in the following cases:', content: ['You authorize the relevant information published by the platform.', 'The platform provides to the national judicial and administrative organization.', 'The platform provides to affiliates of the platform.', 'When the third party and the platform provide services to users together, the third party provides you with the relevant information required for the service (excluding your bank account information).', 'Based on the need to resolve your civil dispute with the third party, the platform has the right to provide your identity information to the third party.'] }, { title: 'Ⅴ. About the use of deposit', message: 'Deposit is used to secure the related transactions on the platform. If you have a dispute during the transaction and you are determined to be responsible for the dispute and carry out the corresponding behavior, and you do not cooperate, the platform has the right to deal with the deposit, including but not limited to detention, freezing, or paying directly to your counterparty.' }, { title: 'Ⅵ. Links to the third party websites', message: 'In order to achieve identity information review, the platform may include links to the third party websites (such as online banking websites).' }, { title: 'VII. Prohibited or Illegal Use', message: 'Acceptance of all explanations, terms, and conditions of this agreement is a prerequisite for your certification application. You declare and guarantee that you will not apply for certification for any illegal purposes or purposes prohibited by this agreement, its terms, and notices. You must not use certification services in any way that may damage, disable, overload, or impair other websites or services, this platform, or interfere with others use of certified merchant applications. You must not obtain or attempt to obtain any data or information through any means not permitted by this platform.' }, { title: 'VIII. Disclaimer', message: 'The platform assumes no responsibility for personal data and information leakage caused by the following situations:', content: ['Leakage of your personal data caused by your disclosure of your account password to others, failure to properly safeguard your password, sharing your account with others, or any other fault not attributable to this platform.', 'Any impact caused by hacking, computer virus intrusions or outbreaks, technical adjustments by telecommunications departments, government policies or legal controls resulting in shutdown, issues caused by third-party reasons (including force majeure, such as failures in international backbone connections or telecommunications providers, fires, floods, lightning strikes, earthquakes, typhoons, tornadoes, volcanic eruptions, epidemics, widespread contagious diseases, strikes, wars, acts of violence, or similar events), and other causes of certification information leakage, loss, theft, or tampering not due to the fault of this platform.', 'Leakage of bank account information caused by linked external sites (such as online banking) and any resulting legal disputes and consequences.', 'Failure to pass certification or suffer any other losses due to the user providing incorrect, incomplete, or false information to this platform, which is not related to this platform.'] }, { title: 'IX. Special Statement', content: ['The platforms basic information review and margin requirements for certified merchants do not represent that certified merchants are 100% trustworthy, nor do they imply any guarantee relationship between the platform and the certified merchants. Users of this platform must strictly follow the transaction process, thoroughly review the counterpartiesinformation, and communicate extensively to ensure the safety of their transactions and assets! Additionally, given the specific nature of digital asset transactions, you need to pay special attention to anti-money laundering risks and understand your trading counterpartiesidentities in accordance with KYC principles; otherwise, you may face risks such as asset freezing due to criminal behavior by your counterparties.', 'Certified merchants commit that the information they provide to this platform is truthful and legal. If the information is found to be false or illegal, the platform may revoke their certification and withhold their deposit.'] }, { title: 'X. Certification Termination', message: 'If a certified merchant wishes to terminate certification, they must submit an application to this platform. If the certified merchant has no bad records, acts that affect trading security, or other illegal or rule-breaking behaviors during the certification period, the platform will review the application within two business days and transfer the funds from the security deposit account to the operable account of the merchant requesting termination.' }],
